85.6	Constipation	Constipation	Constipation (also known as costiveness, dyschezia, and dyssynergic defaecation) refers to bowel movements that are infrequent or hard to pass. Constipation is a common cause of painful defecation. Severe constipation includes obstipation (failure to pass stools or gas) and fecal impaction (see also Bowel obstruction).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Constipation.JPG/220px-Constipation.JPG
